# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat: A new feature
# * fix: A bug fix
# * docs: Documentation only changes
# * chore: Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools
# * refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# * perf: A code change that improves performance
# * test: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# * ci: Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts
#
# Scope should be the area of the codebase affected (optional)
# Examples: web, api, config, docs, etc.
#
# Subject should be a short, imperative description of the change
# Examples: "add dark mode toggle", "fix connection timeout", "update README"
#
# Body should explain what and why vs. how
# Examples: "This change improves performance by caching database queries"
#
# Footer should contain any information about Breaking Changes
# Examples: "BREAKING CHANGE: API response format has changed"
